cs.AR, cs.DS, cs.ET, cs.PL, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper proposes modifications to FPGA logic cell architecture to improve performance and utilization, which falls under the scope of hardware architecture. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the use of compressor trees and generalized parallel counters (GPCs) for synthesis, which are data structures and algorithms commonly used in digital design. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper proposes modifications to existing FPGA architectures, which can be considered as an emerging technology in the field of digital design. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): Although not the main focus of the paper, the proposed modifications to FPGA logic cell architecture can have implications on the programming languages used for FPGA design. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the backward compatibility of the proposed modifications, which can be considered as a software engineering concern in the context of FPGA design.
